\begin{frame}{A Coincident?}

Using the interplay between the phase of $\psi$ and the assumption
\begin{align}
  {\color{green}\vartheta(x)+\vartheta(1-x)=1}
\end{align}
"quasi-miraculous cancellations`` (Ingrid Daubechies) yield
\begin{enumerate}
 \item $\|\psi\|=1$
 \item $\sum_{j,m}\abs{\langle f, \psi_{j,m}\rangle}^2=\|f\|^2$,
\end{enumerate}
and, hence, that the system
\begin{align}
 \{\psi_{j,m}=2^{j}\psi(2^{j}x - m):j,m \in \mathbb{Z}\}
\end{align}
is an {\color{green}ONB} for $L^2(\R)$.


\begin{center}
 {\color{green}Not by Coincidence! $\leadsto$ multiresolution approximation}
\end{center}
