\begin{frame}{Consequences}
{\color{ZurichBlue} The wavelet revolution:}
The developement of the MRA and a construction of compactly supported wavelets triggered a huge body of further works:

\begin{itemize}
 \item \only<2>{\color{green}}Image and audio denoising,\color{black}
 \item \only<2>{\color{green}}Image compression, e.g. JPEG2000,\color{black}
 \item Calderon's programm, T(1) Theorem, (David and Journe; 1984, Meyer; 1986) 
 \item Inverse problems, e.g. MRI (Lustig, Donoho, Pauly; 2007)
 \item Optimal adaptive discretizations of partial differential equations (Cohen, Dahmen, Devore; 2001),
 \item Deconvolution of astronomical images e.g. of Hubble telescope,
 \item Theory of regularity structures (Hairer; 2013),
